The '''People's Movement Party''' ({{lang-ro|Partidul Mișcarea Populară}}, '''PMP''') is a [[Centre-right politics|centre-right]]<ref name="Cinpoes2015"/> [[list of political parties in Romania|political party in Romania]].

==History==
The PMP was created as a political foundation in March 2013 by supporters of then president [[Traian Băsescu]], following his break with the leadership of the [[Democratic Liberal Party (Romania)|Democratic Liberal Party]] (PDL) around former Senate speaker [[Vasile Blaga]].<ref>{{Citation |url=http://www.nineoclock.ro/basescu-ever-closer-to-the-people%E2%80%99s-movement-pdl-takes-distance-from-him/ |author=Daniela Baragan |title=Basescu ever closer to the People’s Movement, PDL takes distance from him |publisher=NineO'Clock.ro |date=8 April 2013 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130409113230/http://www.nineoclock.ro/basescu-ever-closer-to-the-people%e2%80%99s-movement-pdl-takes-distance-from-him/ |archivedate=9 April 2013 |df= }}</ref> It was transformed into a political party in July 2013<ref name="Act240713">{{Citation |url=http://actmedia.eu/daily/popular-movement-party-pmp-officially-registered/47259 |title=Popular Movement Party (PMP) officially registered |publisher=ActMedia.eu |date=24 July 2013}}</ref> and re-launched on 29 January 2014.<ref>{{Citation |url=http://www.nineoclock.ro/people%E2%80%99s-movement-party-aims-re-launching/ |author=Alina Grigoras |title=People’s Movement Party aims re-launching |publisher=NineO'Clock.ro |date=29 January 2014}}</ref>

The PMP identifies itself as [[Christian democracy|Christian democratic]] and [[Liberalism|liberal]].<ref name="Act240713"/> The new party's chairman after June 2014 was former minister of regional development and tourism and Băsescu's confidante [[Elena Udrea]]. Other notable members include former culture minister [[Theodor Paleologu]], former foreign minister [[Teodor Baconschi]], former minister of education [[Daniel Funeriu]], member of European Parliament (MEP) [[Cristian Preda]],<ref>{{Citation |url=http://www.nineoclock.ro/basescu-starts-electoral-offensive-through-popular-movement/ |author=Alina Grigoras |title=Basescu starts electoral offensive through Popular Movement |publisher=NineO'Clock.ro |date=9 February 2014}}</ref> Băsescu's daughter and MEP [[Elena Băsescu]].<ref>{{Citation |url=http://www.gandul.info/politica/elena-basescu-s-a-inscris-in-pmp-dar-nu-va-candida-la-europarlamentare-cum-s-a-incurcat-eba-la-testul-electoral-12322157 |title=Elena Băsescu s-a înscris în PMP, dar NU va candida la europarlamentare. Cum s-a încurcat EBA la "testul electoral" |publisher=Gândul.info |date=24 March 2014}}</ref> and former Foreign Minister and head of the presidential administration [[Cristian Diaconescu]].<ref>{{Citation |url=http://www.nineoclock.ro/cristian-diaconescu-joins-pmp/ |title=Cristian Diaconescu joins PMP
|publisher=NineOclock.Ro |date=20 May 2014}}</ref>

In the [[2014 European Parliament election in Romania|2014 European election]], the party won 6.2% of the votes and two of Romania's 32 seats. Its [[Member of the European Parliament|Members of the European Parliament]] [[Siegfried Mureșan]] and [[Cristian Preda]] joined the [[European People's Party (European Parliament group)|European People's Party Group]], although Preda has since been expelled from the party. On 12 September 2014, the PMP was admitted as a full member to the [[European People's Party]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=EPP concerned over actions of radical Islamic militant groups and over latest political developments in Romania; welcomes five new member parties |publisher=European People's Party |date=12 September 2014 |url=http://www.epp.eu/epp-concerned-over-actions-radical-islamic-militant-groups-and-over-latest-political-developments |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150413072435/http://www.epp.eu/epp-concerned-over-actions-radical-islamic-militant-groups-and-over-latest-political-developments |archivedate=13 April 2015 |df= }}</ref>

For the [[2014 Romanian presidential election|November 2014 presidential election]], the PMP nominated Elena Udrea. She was also endorsed by the [[Christian Democratic National Peasants' Party]] (PNȚCD). With 5.2% of the popular vote, she was placed fourth and did not qualify for the second round.  The party asked its voters to support [[Klaus Iohannis]] of the [[National Liberal Party (Romania)|National Liberal Party]] in the runoff election.<ref>{{Cite news |title=Udrea ultim îndemn către electoratul PMP pentru a vota cu Iohannis |url=http://www.paginadepolitica.ro/udrea-ultim-indemn-catre-trupele-pmp-pentru-a-vota-cu-johannis/ |newspaper=PaginadePolitică.ro |date=15 November 2014}}</ref>

On 12 July 2016, Traian Băsescu announced that the [[National Union for the Progress of Romania]] (UNPR) would merge with PMP on 20 July 2016.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.mediafax.ro/politic/unpr-fuzioneaza-prin-absorbtie-cu-pmp-basescu-gabriel-oprea-ramane-doar-cu-onoarea-partidul-nu-mai-e-dupa-fuziune-partidul-se-va-numi-partidul-miscarea-populara-15525263|title=UNPR fuzionează prin absorbţie cu PMP/ Băsescu: Gabriel Oprea rămâne doar cu onoarea, partidul nu mai e după fuziune. Partidul se va numi Partidul Mişcarea Populară|publisher=[[Mediafax]]|date=12 July 2016|accessdate=13 July 2016|language=Romanian}}</ref>

